Someone came to fix the floor in my kitchen, so I'm going to pretend I still have a job and work from home while reviewing Too Hot to Handle.
If I can just open this damned file. (Damn OneDrive.)
*pirate voice* I'm here.
And that's when it starts to really show. Great!
His passive-aggressive way of turning my air purifier on full makes me uncomfortable, but it smells like wood shavings, so it's justified even though it's an anti-mask. Plus, I really do need to protect myself, right??
I really want to go back to bed, but I can't until he's gone.
The positive thing is that I've finally finished rereading chapter 4 !
Chapter five is long, but full of suspense. Good work.
Currently doing find-and-replace on … ➡️  ellipsis character, and there are 54 of them in this chapter 😅
But well, I'm sticking with it. The most natural speeches are usually fragmented, especially when people let themselves go emotionally.
The craftsman is vacuuming, with a bit of luck, he'll be done soon.
He's gone out (according to what I hear) to cut something. So I took a peek to see where he is. It's far from finished :(
Only 7 pages left on chapter five. It's still my favorite chapter, and it's pretty well done. A few layout changes, and minor edits to switch to active voice and improve conciseness. That said, I'd really like a break and a cup of tea, but the guy is still tinkering in my kitchen.
He just started vacuuming again. I hope that's a good sign.
The craftsman is gone!
He told me he had done a quote for the entire floor, but the owners were cheap and only paid for the small damaged area near the door. It's clearly much better.
The house is ventilating, and my air purifier is running in the kitchen while I enjoy a cup of tea in the garden !
